TextBody:
Hello Maciej,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support. My name is Emiliano and I’ll be the engineer assisting you with this ticket.

Could you please send me a screenshot of what you are seeing in the package?
I downloaded the package and unzipped it now to check, and I'm able to see the PingCastle.exe.config file.




Inside that file, you need to find this:

 <LicenseSettings
    license="" />
And insert your license there.

Please let me know if you have any question and send me a screenshot of what you see in the folder.

Thank you!
Regards,

Emiliano Kraiñuk
Technical Support Engineer

TextBody:
Hello Maciej,

Thanks for letting me know that you were able to find the file and add the license.

To run PingCastle, please open the PingCastle.exe file.
There you will se a menu, so you can follow it and run it for what you need.

Also, here is the documentation about how to use it, so you can check the options you have:
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/PingCastle_3.3_BasicUser/page/Performing_an_Active_Directory_health_check.html#navPoint_9
​​​​​​​https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/PingCastle_3.3_BasicUser/page/Perform_domain_discovery.html#navPoint_10

At the left, you will find the menu to see other related documents.

Please let me know if you have any question.

Emiliano Kraiñuk
Technical Support Engineer
